msgstr "If the person dies,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.8"
msgid "āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "the monk commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.9"
msgid "Kal­yāṇa­kammassa saggakathaṃ katheti—"
msgstr "If a monk talks about heaven to someone of good behavior, thinking,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.10"
msgid "“imaṃ sutvā adhimutto marissatī”ti,"
msgstr "“Hearing this and being keen on it, theyʼll die,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.11"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.12"
msgid "Taṃ sutvā adhimutto marissāmīti"
msgstr "If the target person hears it, becomes keen on it, and thinks, “I shall die,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.13"
msgid "dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ uppādeti,"
msgstr "and they do something painful,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.14"
msgid "āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "the monk commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.15"
msgid "Marati,"
msgstr "If the person dies,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:73.16"
msgid "āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "the monk commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.4.10" href="#Bu-Pj.3.4.10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.445" href="#ms.445"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.1"
msgid "Ācikkhanā nāma"
msgstr "Information:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.2"
msgid "puṭṭho bhaṇati—"
msgstr "if, being asked, a monk says,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.3"
msgid "“evaṃ marassu."
msgstr "“Die in this way;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.4"
msgid "Yo evaṃ marati so dhanaṃ vā labhati yasaṃ vā labhati saggaṃ vā gacchatī”ti,"
msgstr "anyone who dies like this receives wealth/becomes famous/goes to heaven,”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.5"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.6"
msgid "Tāya ācikkhanāya marissāmīti"
msgstr "If, because of that information, the target person thinks, “I shall die,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.7"
msgid "dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ uppādeti,"
msgstr "and they do something painful,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.8"
msgid "āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "the monk commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.9"
msgid "Marati,"
msgstr "If the person dies,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:74.10"
msgid "āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "the monk commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.446" href="#ms.446"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.1"
msgid "Anusāsanī nāma"
msgstr "Instruction:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.2"
msgid "apuṭṭho bhaṇati—"
msgstr "if, without being asked, a monk says,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.3"
msgid "“evaṃ marassu."
msgstr "“Die in this way;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.4"
msgid "Yo evaṃ marati so dhanaṃ vā labhati yasaṃ vā labhati saggaṃ vā gacchatī”ti,"
msgstr "anyone who dies like this receives wealth/becomes famous/goes to heaven,”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.5"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.6"
msgid "Tāya anusāsaniyā marissāmīti"
msgstr "If, because of that instruction, the target person thinks, “I shall die,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.7"
msgid "dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ uppādeti,"
msgstr "and they do something painful,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.8"
msgid "āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "the monk commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.9"
msgid "Marati,"
msgstr "If the person dies,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:75.10"
msgid "āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "the monk commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.447" href="#ms.447"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.1"
msgid "Saṅketakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "An arranged action:"

#. </strong> 
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.136" href="#bd.1.136"></a> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.2"
msgid "saṅketaṃ karoti purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā rattiṃ vā divā vā—"
msgstr "if a monk makes an arrangement for before the meal or for after the meal, for the night or for the day, telling another person,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.3"
msgid "“tena saṅketena taṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill that person according to this arrangement,”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.4"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.5"
msgid "Tena saṅketena taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the other person kills that person according to that arrangement,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.6"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.7"
msgid "Taṃ saṅketaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills him before or after the arranged time,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.8"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti,"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:76.9"
msgid "vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.448" href="#ms.448"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.1"
msgid "Nimittakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Making a sign:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.2"
msgid "nimittaṃ karoti—"
msgstr "a monk makes a sign."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.3"
msgid "“akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇissāmi bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi sīsaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi, tena nimittena taṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "If he says to another person, “When I wink/raise my eyebrow/nod, at that sign kill that person,”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.4"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.5"
msgid "Tena nimittena taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If, at that sign, the other person kills that person,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.6"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.7"
msgid "Taṃ nimittaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills him before or after the sign,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.8"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti,"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:77.9"
msgid "vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.4.11" href="#Bu-Pj.3.4.11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.449" href="#ms.449"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.3"
msgid "asañcicca"
msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.4"
msgid "ajānantassa"
msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.5"
msgid "namara­ṇādhip­pāyassa"
msgstr "if he is not aiming at death;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.6"
msgid "ummattakassa"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:78.7"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="75"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.450" href="#ms.450"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:79.1"
msgid "Manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kamhi paṭha­ma­bhā­ṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The first section on expulsion in relation to human beings is finished."

#. </p><hr><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:80.1"
msgid "3.1. Vinīta­vatthu­uddāna­gāthā"
msgstr "Case rulings"

#. </h2><div class="uddana"><h5>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:80.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "Mnemonic list"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.79" href="#Vin.3.79"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.451" href="#ms.451"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:81.1"
msgid "Saṃvaṇṇanā nisīdanto,"
msgstr "Praising, sitting down,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:81.2"
msgid "musalo­duk­kha­lena ca;"
msgstr "And with pestle, with mortar;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:81.3"
msgid "Vuḍḍha­pabba­ji­tā­bhisanno,"
msgstr "Gone forth when old, flowing out,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:81.4"
msgid "agga­vī­maṃ­sa­nā­visaṃ."
msgstr "First, experimental poison."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.137" href="#bd.1.137"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.452" href="#ms.452"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:82.1"
msgid "Tayo ca vatthukammehi,"
msgstr "And three with making sites,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:82.2"
msgid "iṭṭhakāhipare tayo;"
msgstr "Another three with bricks;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:82.3"
msgid "Vāsī gopānasī ceva,"
msgstr "An adz, and a rafter,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:82.4"
msgid "aṭṭakotaraṇaṃ pati."
msgstr "A elevated platform, coming down, fell down."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.453" href="#ms.453"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:83.1"
msgid "Sedaṃ natthuñca sambāho,"
msgstr "Sweating, and nose treatment, massage,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:83.2"
msgid "nhāpanab­bhañ­ja­nena ca;"
msgstr "By bathing, and by smearing;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:83.3"
msgid "Uṭṭhāpento nipātento,"
msgstr "Making get up, making lie down,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:83.4"
msgid "annapānena māraṇaṃ."
msgstr "Death through food, through drink."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.454" href="#ms.454"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:84.1"
msgid "Jāragabbho sapattī ca,"
msgstr "Child by a lover, and co-wives,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:84.2"
msgid "mātā puttaṃ ubho vadhi;"
msgstr "Mother, child, he killed both;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:84.3"
msgid "Ubho na miyyare maddā,"
msgstr "He killed neither, crushing,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:84.4"
msgid "tāpaṃ vañjhā vijāyinī."
msgstr "Heating, barren, fertile."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.455" href="#ms.455"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:85.1"
msgid "Patodaṃ niggahe yakkho,"
msgstr "Tickling, in taking hold of, a spirit,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:85.2"
msgid "vāḷayakkhañca pāhiṇi;"
msgstr "Wild animals, and spirits, sent;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:85.3"
msgid "Taṃ maññamāno pahari,"
msgstr "Thinking it was him, he gave a blow,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:85.4"
msgid "saggañca nirayaṃ bhaṇe."
msgstr "In talking about heaven, and about hell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.456" href="#ms.456"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:86.1"
msgid "Āḷaviyā tayo rukkhā,"
msgstr "Three trees at Āḷavī,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:86.2"
msgid "dāyehi apare tayo;"
msgstr "Three others with forest groves;"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:86.3"
msgid "Mā kilamesi na tuyhaṃ,"
msgstr "Do not torture, not as you,"

#. <br> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:86.4"
msgid "takkaṃ sovīrakena cāti."
msgstr "Buttermilk, and salty medicine."

#. </p></div><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:87.1"
msgid "3.2. Vinītavatthu"
msgstr "Case details"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="82"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.3.5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.5.1" href="#Bu-Pj.3.5.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.457" href="#ms.457"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti."
msgstr "On one occasion, a certain monk was sick."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.2"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū kāruññena maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇesuṃ."
msgstr "Feeling compassion, the monks praised death to him."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.3"
msgid "So bhikkhu kālamakāsi."
msgstr "He died."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ ahosi"
msgstr "They became remorseful"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.5"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, kacci nu kho mayaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpannā”ti?"
msgstr " and said, “Could it be that we’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.6"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They informed the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.7"
msgid "“Āpattiṃ tumhe, bhikkhave, āpannā pārājikan”ti."
msgstr " and he said, “You have committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:88.8"
msgid "(1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="83"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.5.2" href="#Bu-Pj.3.5.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.458" href="#ms.458"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu pīṭhake pilotikāya paṭicchannaṃ dārakaṃ nisīdanto ottharitvā"
msgstr "On one occasion, a monk who was an almsgoer sat down on a bench, crushing a boy who was concealed by a rag."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.2"
msgid "māresi."
msgstr "The boy died."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.138" href="#bd.1.138"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.3"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.4"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, kacci nu kho ahaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno”ti?"
msgstr "and thought, “Could it be that I’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He informed the Master, and he said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.6"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, pārājikassa."
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion."

#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.7"
msgid "Na ca, bhikkhave, appa­ṭi­vek­khitvā āsane nisīditabbaṃ;"
msgstr "But you should not sit down on a seat without checking it."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.8"
msgid "yo nisīdeyya,"
msgstr "If you do,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.9"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:89.10"
msgid "(2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.5.3" href="#Bu-Pj.3.5.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.459" href="#ms.459"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhattagge antaraghare āsanaṃ paññapento musale ussite ekaṃ musalaṃ aggahesi."
msgstr "On one occasion, a monk was preparing a seat in a dining hall in an inhabited area."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.2"
msgid "Dutiyo musalo paripatitvā aññatarassa dārakassa matthake avatthāsi."
msgstr "When he took hold of a pestle high up, a second pestle fell down, hitting a boy,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.3"
msgid "So kālamakāsi."
msgstr "who then died."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.4"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.5"
msgid "“kiṃcitto tvaṃ, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“What was your intention?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.6"
msgid "“Asañcicca ahaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I didn’t intend it, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.7"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, asañciccā”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no offense when it’s unintentional.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:90.8"
msgid "(3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.460" href="#ms.460"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhattagge antaraghare āsanaṃ paññapento"
msgstr "On one occasion, a monk was preparing a seat in a dining hall in an inhabited area."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.2"
msgid "uduk­kha­la­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ akkamitvā pavaṭṭesi."
msgstr "He stepped on the implements belonging to a mortar."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.3"
msgid "Aññataraṃ dārakaṃ ottharitvā"
msgstr "They fell and hit a boy,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.4"
msgid "māresi."
msgstr "who then died."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.5"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.6"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, asañciccā”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no offense when it’s unintentional.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:91.7"
msgid "(4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.3.5.4" href="#Bu-Pj.3.5.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.461" href="#ms.461"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:92.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pitāputtā bhikkhūsu pabbajitā honti."
msgstr "At one time, there was a father and son who had gone forth with the monks."

#. <span class="note" hidden>“For a certain event” is not found in the Pali, but has been added to make the Pali idiom clearer.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:92.2"
msgid "Kāle ārocite putto pitaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "When the time was announced for a certain event, the son said to his father, "

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.139" href="#bd.1.139"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:92.3"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, saṃgho taṃ patimānetī”ti piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "“Go, Venerable, the Order is waiting for you,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj3:92.4"
msgid "piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "and seizing him by the back, he pushed him."

